# Example environment variables for thehardparts.dev.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` for local development, or set the variables
# below in the Cloudflare Pages project Build settings for production.
# Astro/Vite only exposes variables prefixed with `PUBLIC_` to the
# client-side bundle; everything else is server/build-only (and since
# this site ships as pure static files, "server" just means build-time).

# Cloudflare Web Analytics — beacon token.
#
# How to obtain: Cloudflare dashboard → Analytics & Logs → Web
# Analytics → Add a site → thehardparts.dev. Cloudflare issues a
# beacon token (a short public string, NOT an account secret). Copy
# it here or into the Pages project env vars.
#
# When this variable is unset, BaseLayout omits the beacon `<script>`
# entirely, so local dev stays analytics-free automatically.
#
# If you instead rely on Cloudflare Pages' automatic beacon injection
# (via the Pages project dashboard → Settings → Analytics → Web
# Analytics), leave this unset to avoid emitting the beacon twice.
PUBLIC_CF_BEACON_TOKEN=
